    • Constructor Detail

      • SAT4JSolver

        public SAT4JSolver()
        Constructs a SAT4JSolver that automatically computes the number of variables for each problem. This constructor is equivalent to invoking SAT4JSolver(int) with MAXLITERAL_AUTO as argument.

      • SAT4JSolver

        public SAT4JSolver(int maxLiteral)
        Constructs a SAT4JSolver that defines maxLiteral variables when solving each problem. If the actual number of variables in a problem is less than maxLiteral, the remaining variables are generated automatically.
        Parameters:
        maxLiteral - a positive integer indicating a fixed number of variables for problems handled by this SAT4JSolver, or MAXLITERAL_AUTO if the number of variables should be computed automatically for each problem.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if maxLiteral is nor a positive value neither equal to MAXLITERAL_AUTO.

    • Method Detail

      • setMaxLiteral

        public void setMaxLiteral(int maxLiteral)
        Sets the number of variables for problems handled by this solver.
        Parameters:
        maxLiteral - if positive, each problem handled by this solver will be treated as having a number of variables equal to this value. If MAXLITERAL_AUTO, the number of variables is computed automatically for each problem.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if maxLiteral is nor a positive value neither equal to MAXLITERAL_AUTO.

      • solveSAT

        public java.util.stream.Stream<DimacsLiterals> solveSAT(BooleanFormula problem)
        Solves a boolean satisfiability problem expressed in DIMACS CNF format. If the maxLiteral parameter has been set using setMaxLiteral(int) the solver will use maxLiteral as the total number of variables in the boolean problem, otherwise the actual number of variables in problem will be used.
        Parameters:
        problem -
        Returns:
        the satisfiable models for the input problem, or an empty Stream if the problem is unsatisfiable

      • solvePseudoBoolean

        public java.util.Optional<DimacsLiterals> solvePseudoBoolean(BooleanFormula constraints,
                                                             java.util.stream.IntStream objective)
        Solves a pseudo-boolean problem. The constraints parameter is expressed as a set of DIMACS boolean clauses that are converted internally into linear constraints of the form: 
            sum(Pi for each positive variable Pi in the clause)
 +  sum((1-Qi) for each negated variable Qi in the clause)
 >= 1
        The objective parameter is a a stream of integer coefficients c1, c2, … representing the objective function: 
        min c1*X1 + c2*X2 + …
        for each boolean variable Xi.
        Parameters:
        constraints -
        objective -
        Returns:
        a model that minimizes the objective function, or an empty Optional if the constraints are unsatisfiable
